snippet.textDisplay: Originally written by Amir Khusro. Language is Brij Bhasha an early version of hindi/urdu. The poet is talking about how the 'beloved' transformed him into the form of the 'beloved' itself by merely looking at him. The word beloved can have any meaning you feel like. It can be Allah, your lover or your teacher as probably the case in this song. Khusro can be called a forefather of the sufi music. The amazing thing about his style that he was a muslim sufi mystic poet, a disciple of Khwaja Nizamuddin Auliya, but inspiration from the hindu folk songs about love of Radha and Krishna is clearly there.
